children.subject:
61C, 188, and 186 are my three techs.

Woops...I worded my post wrong, dropping the literature class leaves me at 3 techs

I'm doing something somewhat similar. 186 is supposed to be the least time consuming design course. 188 also really isn't that bad. I think you can manage it without dropping any courses, but try it out for a couple of weeks and see how it pans out. You always have the option to drop, but having taken 61c and 188, I think it's manageable

61C for me was an absolute killer workload, and from what I've heard, the amount of information in 186+61C can be a bit overwhelming. I took 188 this summer and even at 2x speed it was doable, but there are 6 projects and weekly homeworks. For 61C there are another 5 fairly long projects, some of which are split up into 2 parts (with basically 1 part or a full project for every week of the semester). Among all 3 classes, you'll always be working on at least 2 projects and often times 3 + homework + actually trying to learn. For me, 188+61C took some studying to learn the material really well, even though the workloads weren't crazy. Just my two cents.
I see.. that's quite daunting. Thanks everyone for the info, it's been helpful!

As a point of reference:

I took 186 with 189 and 162.

Took 188 with 170 and 168.
Did you have a 4th class, or were they your only classes for those semesters?

With 188 + 170 + 168, there was another math class.

186 + 189 + 162 were the only classes for me that semester, but I also worked 20 hr / week...

You took 4 technicals?? And then a 20hr/week part time job? ...You're amazing..

For the semester where you worked part time, did you manage a reasonable amount of sleep, say 8-10 hours every day, or was it much more hectic? Thank again for everyone's advice.

I find the literature class fairly boring as well, but I'm really not sure about the potential workload of so many techs, so I'd like some advice. Thanks!
